answerText: "Snake"[10] "Snake" is by this English author whose other poems include "Bavarian Gentians" and "The Ship of Death".

question: Question:  [10] Name this poem whose speaker throws a "clumsy log" at the title creature at his water trough and thus "missed my chance with one of the lords of life."
